Mefisto-FLUIDER solve the 2d or 3d STOKES problem for an
incompressible fluid, steady or unsteady, by Brezzi-Fortin or 
Taylor-Hood finite elements(triangle in 2D, tetraedre in 3D).

To compute
. the velocity ui(t,X) i=1,...,d with d=2 or 3
. the pressure p(t,X)
solution of the unsteady Navier-stokes problem:

Mass ( dui/dt + Sum uj dui/dxj ) - Viscos Laplacian ui + CoefPres dp/dxi = FOi i=1,d
div u = Som dui/dxi = 0  in the fluid

with the boundary conditions of the fluid
ui = uDi on the boundary GammaD
Viscos Som dui/duj nj = FGi on the boundary GammaN
p = pD  on the boundary GammaDP

and the initial conditions
ui=u0i i=1,d  in the fluid and its boundary
pi=p0         in the fluid and its boundary

Cf  the documentation Mefisto-Fluider (file fluider.ps),
Cf  the test files pipe2d pipe3d of $MEFISTO/testf
and the test files cavity2d, cylball, marche, ns2d, ns3d,
pipe3d, recyl, step, tube2d, tube3d of $MEFISTO/testa
executable by the typing of readf FileName;

If the problem is dependent of time, the integration is done with 
a one constant step scheme in time, theorically unconditionnaly  stable.
In fact, it is necessary to choose a time step dt such that during dt
a fluid particule does not go through more one layer of finite elements.

To solve the problem, it is necessary
- to have construct the mesh (triangles or tetrahedra) of the fluid,
  an object for Mefisto and interpolated it 
  either the choice of a P1-Lagrange interpolation for Brezzi-Fortin finite elements.
  or     the choice of a P2-Lagrange interpolation for Taylor-Hood finite elements.
- to give the physical characteristics of the fluid mass, viscosity, pressure
  coefficient, force and boundary conditions and initial conditions;
- to choose what problem to solve and the scheme, Stokes or Navier-Stokes,
  steady or unsteady, direct method or fractional steps;
- to visualize the velocities and pressures, ...

Cf https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/NSROLL/NSROLL.html

